          <!--msthemelist--><tr>
            <!--msthemelist--><td valign="baseline" width="42"><img src="../images/anabull1.gif" width="15" height="15" hspace="13"></td>
            <td valign="top" width="100%"><!--mstheme--><font face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica"><!--mstheme--></font>
    <h2 align="left"><!--mstheme--><font face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" color="#336633"><font color="#0000FF">Video Card</font><!--mstheme--></font></h2>
              <!--mstheme--><font face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica"><!--mstheme--></font>
              <!--msthemelist--><table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
                <!--msthemelist--><tr>
                  <!--msthemelist--><td valign="baseline" width="42"><img src="../images/anabull2.gif" width="12" height="12" hspace="15"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="100%"><!--mstheme--><font face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica"><!--mstheme--></font>
        <h3 align="left"><!--mstheme--><font face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" color="#336633"><font color="#0000FF">ATI Radeon 9200</font><!--mstheme--></font></h3>
                    <!--mstheme--><font face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica">
        <p style="line-height: 100%"><font face="Comic Sans MS">To get ATI Radeon 9200 card to work under Redhat
        Linux, follow these instructions (courtesy <a href="http://users.actrix.co.nz/michael/index.html" target="_blank">http://users.actrix.co.nz/michael/index.html</a>):</font>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p style="line-height: 100%">Shutdown X-Windows graphical login daemon, log in on a console as
            root and use telinit:<!--mstheme--></font>
            <pre><font color="#FF0000"># telinit 3</font>    </pre>
          <!--mstheme--><font face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica">
          <li>I'd been using the Radeon binary driver, so I had to restore my
            XFree86 and Mesa OpenGL libraries and modules. If you haven't
            touched these, then this step isn't necessary:
            <div align="justify">
            <!--mstheme--></font>
            <pre style="word-spacing: 0; line-height: 100%; margin-bottom: 0"><font color="#FF0000">rpm --install --force /mnt/cdrom/RedHat/RPMS/</font></pre>
            <!--mstheme--><font face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica">
            </div>
            <div align="justify">
            <!--mstheme--></font>
            <pre style="word-spacing: 0; line-height: 100%; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font color="#FF0000">	XFree86-4.3.0-2.i386.rpm
rpm --install --force /mnt/cdrom/RedHat/RPMS/</font></pre>
            <!--mstheme--><font face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica">
            </div>
            <div align="justify">
            <!--mstheme--></font>
            <pre style="word-spacing: 0; line-height: 100%; margin-top: 0"><font color="#FF0000">	XFree86-Mesa-libGL-4.3.0-2.i386.rpm</font></pre>
            <!--mstheme--><font face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica">
            </div>
          <li>Back up your existing setup.
            <div align="justify">
            <!--mstheme--></font>
            <pre style="word-spacing: 0; line-height: 100%; margin-top: 6; margin-bottom: 0"><font color="#FF0000"># cp /etc/X11/XF86Config /etc/X11/</font></pre>
            <!--mstheme--><font face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica">
            </div>
            <div align="justify">
            <!--mstheme--></font>
            <pre style="line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin-top: 0"><font color="#FF0000">	XF86Config.before-radeon-9200</font></pre>
            <!--mstheme--><font face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica">
            </div>
          <li>Run redhat-config-xfree86 and setup the card as a Radeon 9000.
            Under advanced option, use the configure button to choose the video
            card - I picked the <em>ATI Radeon 9000</em>. Tick the checkbox to <em>Enable
            Hardware 3D Acceleration.</em> Don't probe, we just want the config
            program to create a valid XFree86 config - we have to change the
            ChipId before we can try it.<!--mstheme--></font>
            <pre><font color="#FF0000"># redhat-config-xfree86</font>      </pre>
          <!--mstheme--><font face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica">
          <li>Edit the config file and set the ChipId<!--mstheme--></font>
            <pre><font color="#FF0000"># vi /etc/X11/XF86Config</font>          </pre>
          <!--mstheme--><font face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica">
            Find the device setion and add the ChipId:<!--mstheme--></font>
            <pre><font color="#FF0000">Section &quot;Device&quot;
        Identifier  &quot;Videocard0&quot;
        Driver      &quot;radeon&quot;
        VendorName  &quot;Videocard vendor&quot;
        BoardName   &quot;ATI Radeon 9000&quot;
        ChipId      0x514D
EndSection</font></pre>
          <!--mstheme--><font face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica">
          <li>Test the new configuration for both 2D and 3D. Do a few syncs
            before hand in case your system locks up.<!--mstheme--></font>
            <pre><font color="#FF0000"># sync; sync; sync; 
# startx</font></pre>
          <!--mstheme--><font face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica">
            You can try glxinfo and confirm DRI for 3D is enabled:<!--mstheme--></font>
            <pre><font color="#FF0000"># glxinfo
display: :0.0  screen:0
direct rendering: Yes</font></pre>
          <!--mstheme--><font face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica">
          <li>Restart the graphical login daemon<!--mstheme--></font>
            <pre><font color="#FF0000"># telinit 5</font>   </pre>
          <!--mstheme--><font face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica">
          </li>
        </ol>
                    <!--mstheme--></font><!--msthemelist--></td>
                </tr>
              <!--msthemelist--></table>
              <!--mstheme--><font face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica"><!--mstheme--></font><!--msthemelist--></td>
          </tr>
          <!--msthemelist--><tr>
            <!--msthemelist--><td valign="baseline" width="42"><img src="../images/anabull1.gif" width="15" height="15" hspace="13"></td>
            <td valign="top" width="100%"><!--mstheme--><font face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica"><!--mstheme--></font>
    <h2 align="left"><!--mstheme--><font face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" color="#336633"><font color="#0000FF">Web server stuff</font><!--mstheme--></font></h2>
              <!--mstheme--><font face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica"><!--mstheme--></font>
              <!--msthemelist--><table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
                <!--msthemelist--><tr>
                  <!--msthemelist--><td valign="baseline" width="42"><img src="../images/anabull2.gif" width="12" height="12" hspace="15"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="100%"><!--mstheme--><font face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica"><!--mstheme--></font>
        <h3 align="left" style="line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><!--mstheme--><font face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" color="#336633"><font color="#0000FF">PHP v 4.3.x</font><!--mstheme--></font></h3>
                    <!--mstheme--><font face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica"><!--mstheme--></font><!--msthemelist--></td>
                </tr>
              <!--msthemelist--></table>
              <!--mstheme--><font face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica">
<blockquote>
  <blockquote>
    <p style="word-spacing: 0; line-height: 100%; margin-top: 0" align="justify">To compile PHP v 4.3.x under Redhat 9.0,
    download the PHP source code
    from <a href="http://www.php.net/releases.php" target="_blank">here</a>. (Note that for
    Apache 2.0.40 which comes with Redhat 9.0 or its updated kernel version
    2.4.31, you need PHP 4.3.0. The other version will require you to install
    newer version of apache. </p>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 0">Untar the source code:</li>
    </ol>
    <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;
    &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <font color="#FF0000"># tar
    xvfz php-4.3.x.tar.gz</font></p>
    <ol start="2">
      <li>
        <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">Configure the system</li>
    </ol>
    <blockquote>
      <p style="margin-bottom: 0"><font color="#FF0000">#
      ./configure --with-apxs2=/usr/sbin/apxs --with-gd --with-jpeg-dir=/usr
      --with-mysql=/usr --with-zlib-dir=/usr --enable-sigchild</font></p>
    </blockquote>
	or for the way rehat installs php use the following command:
    <blockquote>
      <p style="margin-bottom: 0"><font color="#FF0000">#
      ./configure --host=i386-redhat-linux --build=i386-redhat-linux --target=i386-redhat-linux-gnu --program-prefix= --prefix=/usr --exec-prefix=/usr --bindir=/usr/bin --sbindir=/usr/sbin --sysconfdir=/etc --datadir=/usr/share --includedir=/usr/include --libdir=/usr/lib --libexecdir=/usr/libexec --localstatedir=/var --sharedstatedir=/usr/com --mandir=/usr/share/man --infodir=/usr/share/info --cache-file=../config.cache --with-config-file-path=/etc --with-config-file-scan-dir=/etc/php.d --enable-force-cgi-redirect --disable-debug --enable-pic --disable-rpath --enable-inline-optimization --with-bz2 --with-db3 --with-curl --with-dom=/usr --with-exec-dir=/usr/bin --with-freetype-dir=/usr --with-png-dir=/usr --with-gd --enable-gd-native-ttf --with-ttf --with-gdbm --with-gettext --with-ncurses --with-gmp --with-iconv --with-jpeg-dir=/usr --with-png --with-pspell --with-regex=system --with-xml --with-expat-dir=/usr --with-zlib --with-layout=GNU --enable-bcmath --enable-exif --enable-ftp --enable-magic-quotes --enable-safe-mode --enable-sockets --enable-sysvsem --enable-sysvshm --enable-discard-path --enable-track-vars --enable-trans-sid --enable-yp --enable-wddx --without-oci8 --with-pear=/usr/share/pear --with-imap=shared --with-imap-ssl --with-kerberos=/usr/kerberos --with-ldap=shared --with-mysql=shared,/usr --with-pgsql=shared --with-snmp=shared,/usr --with-snmp=shared --enable-ucd-snmp-hack --with-unixODBC=shared --enable-memory-limit --enable-bcmath --enable-shmop --enable-versioning --enable-calendar --enable-dbx --enable-dio --enable-mcal --enable-force-cgi-redirect --with-apxs2=/usr/sbin/apxs --with-zlib-dir=/usr --enable-sigchild </font></p>
    </blockquote>
    <ol>
      <li value="3">
        <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">Make and install PHP. After
        installing do a restart on httpd:</li>
    </ol>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;
    &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <font color="#FF0000"># make &amp;&amp; make
    install</font></p>
    <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;&nbsp;
    &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <font color="#FF0000"># service httpd restart</font></p>
  </blockquote>
</blockquote>

              <!--mstheme--></font><!--msthemelist--></td>
          </tr>
        <!--msthemelist--></table>
        <!--mstheme--><font face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica"><!--mstheme--></font></td>
    </tr>
  </table><!--mstheme--><font face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica">
